Coding:
    stiltc:
        
    stilts-stdlib:
        Native:
            Threadpool
            String functions
                find, findIdx, rfind, rfindIdx
                contains
                clear, resize
                split, splitFirst, splitLast
                replace, replaceFirst, replaceLast
                trim
                startsWith, endsWith
                append
                swap
                substring
                insert
                format
                toUpper, toLower
                hash
                equals
                compareto
            Consistent error behavior
            Configs
        Stilts:
            Basic types
            Mutex
            RWLock
            Atomic<T>
            String
            UTF8String
            PythonObject like Swift?
            Collections Framework:
                Iterators:
                    trait Iterable<T>                              (Base of framework, can produce an Iterator<T>)
                    trait RandomIterable<T>       impl Iterable<T>
                    trait Iterator<T>             impl Iterable<T> (Supports Stream ops)
                    trait RandomIterator<T>       impl Iterator<T>
                Collections:
                    trait Collection<T>           impl Iterable<T>
                    class Array<T, size>          impl Collection<T>, RandomIterable<T>
                    class List<T>                 impl Collection<T>, RandomIterable<T>
                Other:
                    trait Hashable
                    class Map<K impl Hashable, V> impl Collection<Pair<K, V>>
                    class Set<T impl Hashable>    impl Collection<T> (Backed by a Map<T, T>)
                
    apaz-libc:
        readFile macro wrap for memdebug
        List reduce()
        String to/from integral types (with error checking)
